#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.63"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.63:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:0.2"
msgid "6. Abyākatavagga "
msgstr "6. The Undeclared Points "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 63. Bhariyāsutta → sattabhariyāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.63:0.3"
msgid "63. Bhariyāsutta "
msgstr "63. Kinds of Wives "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an7.63:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the householder Anāthapiṇḍika, where he sat on the seat spread out. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa nivesane manussā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā honti. "
msgstr "Now at that time people in Anāthapiṇḍika’s home were making a dreadful racket. "

msgctxt "an7.63:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him, "

#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.63:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu te, gahapati, nivesane manussā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā kevaṭṭā maññe macchavilope”ti? "
msgstr "“Householder, what’s with the people making that dreadful racket in your home? You’d think it was fishermen hauling in a catch!” "

# NOTE: Note BB follow’s PTS reading of an extra addha.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:2.2"
msgid "“Ayaṃ, bhante, sujātā gharasuṇhā aḍḍhakulā ānītā. "
msgstr "“Sir, that’s my daughter-in-law Sujātā. She’s been brought here from a wealthy family. "

# NOTE: The politics of the relations here are important. The word used is adiyati. This is used in the same sense in DN 32, where it refers to yakkhas rebelling against the gods, or bandits rebelling against the the king. So “obey” seems fine, perhaps we could use “submit”. Note that this is not a general problem, but specifically living under another’s roof. Note too that the relation with the Buddha is of respect, not obedience, and it is this that actually works!
msgctxt "an7.63:2.3"
msgid "Sā neva sassuṃ ādiyati, na sasuraṃ ādiyati, na sāmikaṃ ādiyati, bhagavantampi na sakkaroti na garuṃ karoti na māneti na pūjetī”ti. "
msgstr "She doesn’t obey her mother-in-law or father-in-law or her husband. And she does not honor, respect, esteem, and venerate the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.92, sc3
msgctxt "an7.63:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sujātaṃ gharasuṇhaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Sujātā, saying, "

# NOTE: Note the Buddha’s usual style: deal directly with the person themselves in a respectful manner.
msgctxt "an7.63:3.2"
msgid "“ehi, sujāte”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, Sujātā.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:3.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho sujātā gharasuṇhā bhagavato paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sujātaṃ gharasuṇhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” she replied. She went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to her: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an7.63:4.1"
msgid "“Satta kho imā, sujāte, purisassa bhariyāyo. "
msgstr "“Sujātā, a man can have seven kinds of wife. "

msgctxt "an7.63:4.2"
msgid "Katamā satta? "
msgstr "What seven? "

msgctxt "an7.63:4.3"
msgid "Vadhakasamā, corīsamā, ayyasamā, mātāsamā, bhaginīsamā, sakhīsamā, dāsīsamā. "
msgstr "A wife like a killer, a wife like a thief, a wife like a lord, a wife like a mother, a wife like a sister, a wife like a friend, and a wife like a bondservant. "

msgctxt "an7.63:4.4"
msgid "Imā kho, sujāte, satta purisassa bhariyāyo. "
msgstr "These are the kinds of wife that a man can have. "

msgctxt "an7.63:4.5"
msgid "Tāsaṃ tvaṃ katamā”ti? "
msgstr "Which one of these are you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: ahaṃ → nāhaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.63:4.6"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, bhante, imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi. "
msgstr "“Sir, I don’t understand the detailed meaning of what the Buddha has said in brief. "

msgctxt "an7.63:4.7"
msgid "Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathāhaṃ imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ jāneyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Please teach me this matter so I can understand the detailed meaning.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:4.8"
msgid "“Tena hi, sujāte, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Sujātā, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:4.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho sujātā gharasuṇhā bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” she replied. "

msgctxt "an7.63:4.10"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an7.63:5.1"
msgid "“Paduṭṭhacittā ahitānukampinī, "
msgstr "“With a mind full of hate and no kindness, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:5.2"
msgid "Aññesu rattā atimaññate patiṃ; "
msgstr "lusting for others, looking down on her husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:5.3"
msgid "Dhanena kītassa vadhāya ussukā, "
msgstr "she longs to murder the one who paid the price for her. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:5.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:5.5"
msgid "‘Vadhā ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (1) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a killer. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an7.63:6.1"
msgid "Yaṃ itthiyā vindati sāmiko dhanaṃ, "
msgstr "A woman’s husband earns his wealth "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:6.2"
msgid "Sippaṃ vaṇijjañca kasiṃ adhiṭṭhahaṃ; "
msgstr "by applying oneself to a profession, trade, or farming. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:6.3"
msgid "Appampi tassa apahātumicchati, "
msgstr "And even if it’s only a little, she wants to take it. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:6.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:6.5"
msgid "‘Corī ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (2) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a thief. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an7.63:7.1"
msgid "Akammakāmā alasā mahagghasā, "
msgstr "She’s an idle glutton who doesn’t want to work. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:7.2"
msgid "Pharusā ca caṇḍī duruttavādinī; "
msgstr "Her words are harsh, fierce, and rude. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:7.3"
msgid "Uṭṭhāyakānaṃ abhibhuyya vattati, "
msgstr "She rules over him, though he rises early. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:7.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:7.5"
msgid "‘Ayyā ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (3) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a lord. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.93, sc8
msgctxt "an7.63:8.1"
msgid "Yā sabbadā hoti hitānukampinī, "
msgstr "She’s always caring and kind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:8.2"
msgid "Mātāva puttaṃ anurakkhate patiṃ; "
msgstr "looking after her husband like a mother her child. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:8.3"
msgid "Tato dhanaṃ sambhatamassa rakkhati, "
msgstr "She keeps the wealth that he has earned secure. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:8.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:8.5"
msgid "‘Mātā ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (4) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a mother. "

# NOTE: Not sure why BB reads “elder brother” here. It seems to me it could be either “elders” or “elder sister”. The verse doesn’t appear elsewhere, and Comm says nothing. Hare has “elder born”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: kaniṭṭhakā → kaniṭṭhā (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.63:9.1"
msgid "Yathāpi jeṭṭhā bhaginī kaniṭṭhakā, "
msgstr "She respects her husband "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:9.2"
msgid "Sagāravā hoti sakamhi sāmike; "
msgstr "as a younger sister respects her elder. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:9.3"
msgid "Hirīmanā bhattuvasānuvattinī, "
msgstr "Conscientious, she does what her husband says. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:9.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:9.5"
msgid "‘Bhaginī ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (5) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a sister. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an7.63:10.1"
msgid "Yācīdha disvāna patiṃ pamodati, "
msgstr "She’s delighted to see him, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:10.2"
msgid "Sakhī sakhāraṃva cirassamāgataṃ; "
msgstr "like one reunited with a long-lost friend. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:10.3"
msgid "Koleyyakā sīlavatī patibbatā, "
msgstr "She’s well-raised, virtuous, and devoted. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:10.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:10.5"
msgid "‘Sakhī ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (6) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a friend. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an7.63:11.1"
msgid "Akkuddhasantā vadhadaṇḍatajjitā, "
msgstr "She has no anger when threatened with violence by the rod. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:11.2"
msgid "Aduṭṭhacittā patino titikkhati; "
msgstr "Without hate or anger, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:11.3"
msgid "Akkodhanā bhattuvasānuvattinī, "
msgstr "she endures her husband and does what he says. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:11.4"
msgid "Yā evarūpā purisassa bhariyā; "
msgstr "A man’s wife of this sort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:11.5"
msgid "‘Dāsī ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati. (7) "
msgstr "is called a wife and a bondservant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an7.63:12.1"
msgid "Yācīdha bhariyā vadhakāti vuccati, "
msgstr "The kinds of wives here called "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:12.2"
msgid "‘Corī ca ayyā’ti ca yā pavuccati; "
msgstr "killer, thief, and lord; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:12.3"
msgid "Dussīlarūpā pharusā anādarā, "
msgstr "unethical, harsh, and lacking regard for others, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:12.4"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā nirayaṃ vajanti tā. (1–3.) "
msgstr "when their body breaks up they go to hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an7.63:13.1"
msgid "Yācīdha mātā bhaginī sakhīti ca, "
msgstr "But the kinds of wives here called "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:13.2"
msgid "‘Dāsī ca bhariyā’ti ca sā pavuccati; "
msgstr "mother, sister, friend, and bondservant; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:13.3"
msgid "Sīle ṭhitattā cirarattasaṃvutā, "
msgstr "steadfast in their own morality, restrained for a long time, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.63:13.4"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā sugatiṃ vajanti tāti. (4–7.) "
msgstr "when their body breaks up they go to a good place. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.94, sc14
msgctxt "an7.63:14.1"
msgid "Imā kho, sujāte, satta purisassa bhariyāyo. "
msgstr "Sujātā, these are the seven kinds of wife that a man can have. "

msgctxt "an7.63:14.2"
msgid "Tāsaṃ tvaṃ katamā”ti? "
msgstr "Which one of these are you?” "

# NOTE: Yuk. Perhaps the most harmful sutta in the Pali canon. It unfortunately has several Chinese parallels, which, so far as a quick survey shows, all have her wanting to be a slave, and to consent to violence. I’ll go and have a little cry now.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.63:14.3"
msgid "“Ajjatagge maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dāsīsamaṃ sāmikassa bhariyaṃ dhāretū”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, from this day forth may the Buddha remember me as a wife like a bondservant.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.63:14.4"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

